You're going to pull it back
and forth pretty darn slow

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:33.660
until you see smoke.

00:09:33.660 --> 00:09:34.660
Once you see smoke,

00:09:34.660 --> 00:09:36.960
you want to keep
a really even pace.

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:41.400
Now this pace needs to last
for about 30 Strokes.

00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:43.960
So you can kind of count
the ABC's in your head.

00:09:43.960 --> 00:09:45.840
It's about the amount
of time it's going to take,

00:09:45.840 --> 00:09:47.320
and as you do that,

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:50.300
the downward pressure of your
palm rock is very important.

00:09:50.300 --> 00:09:59.840
[Music]

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:01.792
So all that took was
really about 15 seconds.

00:10:01.792 --> 00:10:05.172
You can already see
that they've got some friction,

00:10:05.592 --> 00:10:07.200
and we've already
dark in the wood.

00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:09.200
We've already have
a little bit of smoke.

00:10:09.600 --> 00:10:11.120
So we're going to keep going.

00:10:11.132 --> 00:10:13.023
If at any point you're feeling

00:10:13.023 --> 00:10:16.300
like your bow string just
isn't staying tight enough,

00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:20.780
it's pretty darn easy to take
your leftover paracord here,

00:10:21.152 --> 00:10:23.922
wrap it around
that clove hitch knot,

00:10:24.140 --> 00:10:28.340
and this is why you want
to use the more curved edge

00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:29.680
where your hand is,

00:10:29.680 --> 00:10:32.400
because you can actually
tighten the string as you go.

00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:40.600
[Music]

00:10:40.600 --> 00:10:41.520
At this point, you can see

00:10:41.530 --> 00:10:44.236
that Calli has smoke coming
off of the spindle.

00:10:44.236 --> 00:10:46.923
What you're really looking
for in an ember is

00:10:46.923 --> 00:10:49.517
when you stop using the bow
and the spindle,

00:10:49.517 --> 00:10:52.507
you should see a thin stream
of smoke coming up.

00:10:52.507 --> 00:10:54.480
If you have a successful ember,

00:10:54.480 --> 00:10:57.580
it will continue smoking
after you stop using the bow.

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:02.840
Still smoking, still smoking.

00:11:02.845 --> 00:11:03.611
Okay.

00:11:03.611 --> 00:11:04.552
Here's a chance.

00:11:06.292 --> 00:11:07.830
I may have an ember.

00:11:10.350 --> 00:11:11.811
It's still smoking?

00:11:11.811 --> 00:11:12.642
Little.

00:11:16.788 --> 00:11:18.326
Nope, that one died.

00:11:18.942 --> 00:11:20.622
All right, that's okay.

00:11:20.842 --> 00:11:23.650
Getting it on your first try
doesn't normally happen,

00:11:23.650 --> 00:11:27.072
but you could see
the smoke rising off of it,

00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:28.900
and you can see,

00:11:28.900 --> 00:11:31.120
this has been
a sharpen point before...

00:11:31.280 --> 00:11:32.900
We worked that way...

00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:35.340
Very out of breath.

00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:38.620
We've worked that down
to almost a flat edge now.

00:11:38.620 --> 00:11:41.420
So that's what it looks
like to just a few passes.

00:11:41.420 --> 00:11:42.240
All right, Nate.

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:43.200
I'm tired.

00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:44.660
Wanna give it a shot?

00:11:44.660 --> 00:11:51.480
[Music]

00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:52.460
Nice.

00:11:56.260 --> 00:11:58.260
[inaudible] this one,

00:12:00.900 --> 00:12:01.580
There you go.

00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:02.720
Now, hold it up.

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:04.140
Don't breathe on it,
jus hold it up.

00:12:04.150 --> 00:12:05.072
There you go.

00:12:05.072 --> 00:12:05.750
See that?

00:12:05.750 --> 00:12:07.365
This is what we want.

00:12:07.365 --> 00:12:08.365
He's got one.

00:12:10.680 --> 00:12:12.020
Okay, now stand up,

00:12:12.020 --> 00:12:14.580
and just sort of pass it
through the air back and forth.

00:12:14.980 --> 00:12:18.332
Gently and don't do this
over anything flammable.

00:12:19.660 --> 00:12:20.900
He's got a flame guys.

00:12:20.900 --> 00:12:21.700
He did it.

00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:33.580
[Music]

00:12:33.580 --> 00:12:35.040
I made fire.

00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:37.720
He's advanced to
the level of caveman.

00:12:37.740 --> 00:12:38.760
Yes!

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:41.160
Now, obviously,

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.740
we weren't looking to create
a bonfire here today.

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:46.140
But if you'd had a pile
of kindling ready to go,

00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:49.100
some nice dry wood and tinder,
this would have caught.

00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:50.420
You would have been good to go.

00:12:51.222 --> 00:12:53.579
So it's been a couple of days
since Nate and I showed you

00:12:53.579 --> 00:12:54.800
how to make a bow drill fire.

00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:56.429
Now Grant wants to try.

00:12:56.429 --> 00:12:57.550
What can I say?

00:12:57.550 --> 00:12:58.692
I like fire.

00:12:58.692 --> 00:13:14.740
[Music]

00:13:14.740 --> 00:13:16.620
It's still smoking,
still smoking.

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:18.140
Still smoking.

00:13:18.140 --> 00:13:19.032
Still smoking.

00:13:19.032 --> 00:13:19.752
Okay, cool.

00:13:19.752 --> 00:13:20.594
You got one.

00:13:20.600 --> 00:13:22.400
Didn't say I was the best,

00:13:23.540 --> 00:13:25.900
but I do like making the fire.

00:13:26.180 --> 00:13:28.280
All right, very carefully here.

00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:43.400
[Music]

00:13:43.400 --> 00:13:45.700
It is just a little baby fire
